 ."]},{"name":"Da Cunha","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Portuguese Joao, Joaquim, Afonso, Albano, Almir, Ilidio, Serafim.  Spanish Jose, Manuel, Mario, Carlos, Alvaro, Fernando, Jorge, Rogerio, Alfonso, Alfredo, Armando, Armindo.","Portuguese: variant of   Cunha  , with the addition of <i>da</i>, a shortened form of the preposition <i>de</i> ‘from’ and the feminine definite article <i>a</i> ‘the’."]}]},{"name":"Fernão","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: habitational name from any of various places called Fernau, Fernow, or Viernau."],"variants":[{"name":"Fearnow","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Fernau   or of <b>Virnau</b> (also <b>Viernow</b>), a habitational name from Viernau in Thuringia."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1356752,"age":9,"year":"1112","julianDay":2127209,"description":"Afonso inherits the County of Portugal, a province of Castile.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Fernão Paes da Cunha was born in 1103, in Portugal, his father, D. Payo Guterrez da Cunha, was 36 and his mother, Ausenda Ermiges de Ribadouro, was 52. He married D. Mayor Rendufe about 1140. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1180, in Tábua, Coimbra, Portugal, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1103–1180":"1103–1180","1110–1228":"1110–1228","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1145–1225":"1145–1225","1150–1170":"1150–1170","1067–Male":"1067–Surnud","1052–Female":"1052–Surnud","1228":"1228","ABT 1140":"umbes 1140","1225":"1225","1103":"1103","1145":"1145","1112":"1112","1067":"1067","1110":"1110","1052":"1052","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","PORTUGAL":"Portugal","São Miguel de Cunha, Braga, Portugal":"Braga, Portugal","Tábua, Coimbra, Portugal":"Tábua, Coimbra, Portugal","Portugal":"Portugal"},"fi":{"1103–1180":"1103–1180","1110–1228":"1110–1228","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1145–1225":"1145–1225","1150–1170":"1150–1170","1067–M